{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1577,"text":"I'd like to share with you"},{"time":3573,"text":"the story of one of my patients called Celine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":7410,"text":"Celine is a housewife and lives in a rural district"},{"time":10563,"text":"of Cameroon in west Central Africa."},{"time":13635,"text":"Six years ago, at the time of her HIV diagnosis,"},{"time":17322,"text":"she was recruited to participate in the clinical trial"},{"time":20323,"text":"which was running in her health district at the time."},{"time":23394,"text":"When I first met Celine, a little over a year ago,"},{"time":27098,"text":"she had gone for 18 months"},{"time":28782,"text":"without any antiretroviral therapy,"},{"time":31069,"text":"and she was very ill."},{"time":33806,"text":"She told me that she stopped coming to the clinic"},{"time":36204,"text":"when the trial ended"},{"time":37755,"text":"because she had no money for the bus fare"},{"time":40466,"text":"and was too ill to walk the 35-kilometer distance."},{"time":44194,"text":"Now during the clinical trial,"},{"time":45938,"text":"she'd been given all her antiretroviral drugs free of charge,"},{"time":50323,"text":"and her transportation costs"},{"time":52354,"text":"had been covered by the research funds."},{"time":54961,"text":"All of these ended once the trial was completed,"},{"time":58315,"text":"leaving Celine with no alternatives."},{"time":61307,"text":"She was unable to tell me the names of the drugs"},{"time":63983,"text":"she'd received during the trial,"},{"time":66010,"text":"or even what the trial had been about."},{"time":68767,"text":"I didn't bother to ask her what the results of the trial were"},{"time":72316,"text":"because it seemed obvious to me that she would have no clue."},{"time":76723,"text":"Yet what puzzled me most"},{"time":78992,"text":"was Celine had given her informed consent"},{"time":82099,"text":"to be a part of this trial, yet she clearly did not understand"},{"time":85931,"text":"the implications of being a participant"},{"time":88401,"text":"or what would happen to her once the trial had been completed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92810,"text":"Now, I have shared this story with you as an example"},{"time":96205,"text":"of what can happen to participants in the clinical trial"},{"time":99134,"text":"when it is poorly conducted."},{"time":101593,"text":"Maybe this particular trial yielded exciting results."},{"time":105458,"text":"Maybe it even got published in a high-profile scientific journal."},{"time":109147,"text":"Maybe it would inform clinicians around the world"},{"time":111954,"text":"on how to improve on the clinical management of HIV patients."},{"time":117489,"text":"But it would have done so at a price"},{"time":120275,"text":"to hundreds of patients who, like Celine,"},{"time":123222,"text":"were left to their own devices"},{"time":125466,"text":"once the research had been completed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":128537,"text":"I do not stand here today to suggest in any way"},{"time":131875,"text":"that conducting HIV clinical trials"},{"time":133888,"text":"in developing countries is bad."},{"time":136103,"text":"On the contrary, clinical trials are extremely useful tools,"},{"time":140470,"text":"and are much needed to address the burden"},{"time":142768,"text":"of disease in developing countries."},{"time":145239,"text":"However, the inequalities that exist between"},{"time":148098,"text":"richer countries and developing countries in terms of funding"},{"time":151800,"text":"pose a real risk for exploitation,"},{"time":154957,"text":"especially in the context of externally-funded research."},{"time":158842,"text":"Sadly enough, the fact remains that"},{"time":161448,"text":"a lot of the studies that are conducted in developing countries"},{"time":165432,"text":"could never be authorized in the richer countries"},{"time":168008,"text":"which fund the research."}]},{"cues":[{"time":170256,"text":"I'm sure you must be asking yourselves"},{"time":172503,"text":"what makes developing countries,"},{"time":174419,"text":"especially those in sub-Saharan Africa,"},{"time":176963,"text":"so attractive for these HIV clinical trials?"},{"time":180530,"text":"Well, in order for a clinical trial to generate"},{"time":183802,"text":"valid and widely applicable results,"},{"time":186918,"text":"they need to be conducted with large numbers of study participants"},{"time":190918,"text":"and preferably on a population"},{"time":193561,"text":"with a high incidence of new HIV infections."},{"time":197342,"text":"Sub-Saharan Africa largely fits this description,"},{"time":200813,"text":"with 22 million people living with HIV,"},{"time":204015,"text":"an estimated 70 percent of the 30 million people"},{"time":207655,"text":"who are infected worldwide."},{"time":210136,"text":"Also, research within the continent"},{"time":212566,"text":"is a lot easier to conduct due to widespread poverty,"},{"time":216678,"text":"endemic diseases and inadequate health care systems."},{"time":220529,"text":"A clinical trial that is considered to be"},{"time":223318,"text":"potentially beneficial to the population"},{"time":226068,"text":"is more likely to be authorized,"},{"time":228375,"text":"and in the absence of good health care systems,"},{"time":231175,"text":"almost any offer of medical assistance"},{"time":234129,"text":"is accepted as better than nothing."},{"time":237047,"text":"Even more problematic reasons include"},{"time":239633,"text":"lower risk of litigation,"},{"time":241920,"text":"less rigorous ethical reviews,"},{"time":244387,"text":"and populations that are willing to participate"},{"time":246943,"text":"in almost any study that hints at a cure."},{"time":251607,"text":"As funding for HIV research"},{"time":255232,"text":"increases in developing countries"},{"time":257488,"text":"and ethical review in richer countries become more strict,"},{"time":261495,"text":"you can see why this context becomes"},{"time":263580,"text":"very, very attractive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":266141,"text":"The high prevalence of HIV drives researchers"},{"time":269821,"text":"to conduct research that is sometimes scientifically acceptable"},{"time":274305,"text":"but on many levels ethically questionable."},{"time":277584,"text":"How then can we ensure that, in our search for the cure,"},{"time":281023,"text":"we do not take an unfair advantage"},{"time":283343,"text":"of those who are already most affected by the pandemic?"},{"time":286847,"text":"I invite you to consider four areas I think we can focus on"},{"time":290703,"text":"in order to improve the way in which things are done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294278,"text":"The first of these is informed consent."},{"time":297105,"text":"Now, in order for a clinical trial to be"},{"time":299473,"text":"considered ethically acceptable,"},{"time":303154,"text":"participants must be given the relevant information"},{"time":305978,"text":"in a way in which they can understand,"},{"time":308413,"text":"and must freely consent to participate in the trial."},{"time":312630,"text":"This is especially important in developing countries,"},{"time":315308,"text":"where a lot of participants consent to research"},{"time":318210,"text":"because they believe it is the only way in which"},{"time":320898,"text":"they can receive medical care or other benefits."},{"time":324468,"text":"Consent procedures that are used in richer countries"},{"time":327435,"text":"are often inappropriate or ineffective"},{"time":330237,"text":"in a lot of developing countries."},{"time":332590,"text":"For example, it is counterintuitive to have"},{"time":335563,"text":"an illiterate study participant, like Celine,"},{"time":338562,"text":"sign a lengthy consent form that they are unable to read,"},{"time":341889,"text":"let alone understand."},{"time":343996,"text":"Local communities need to be more involved"},{"time":347076,"text":"in establishing the criteria for recruiting participants"},{"time":350349,"text":"in clinical trials, as well as the incentives for participation."},{"time":355050,"text":"The information in these trials"},{"time":356866,"text":"needs to be given to the potential participants"},{"time":359817,"text":"in linguistically and culturally acceptable formats."}]},{"cues":[{"time":364245,"text":"The second point I would like for you to consider"},{"time":367066,"text":"is the standard of care that is provided"},{"time":369504,"text":"to participants within any clinical trial."},{"time":372450,"text":"Now, this is subject to a lot of debate and controversy."},{"time":376147,"text":"Should the control group in the clinical trial"},{"time":379128,"text":"be given the best current treatment which is available"},{"time":382401,"text":"anywhere in the world?"},{"time":384481,"text":"Or should they be given an alternative standard of care,"},{"time":387449,"text":"such as the best current treatment available"},{"time":390337,"text":"in the country in which the research is being conducted?"},{"time":393649,"text":"Is it fair to evaluate a treatment regimen"},{"time":396989,"text":"which may not be affordable or accessible"},{"time":400065,"text":"to the study participants once the research has been completed?"},{"time":404035,"text":"Now, in a situation where the best current treatment"},{"time":407776,"text":"is inexpensive and simple to deliver,"},{"time":410415,"text":"the answer is straightforward."},{"time":412443,"text":"However, the best current treatment available"},{"time":415593,"text":"anywhere in the world is often very difficult"},{"time":418480,"text":"to provide in developing countries."},{"time":421167,"text":"It is important to assess the potential risks and benefits"},{"time":424719,"text":"of the standard of care which is to be provided"},{"time":427496,"text":"to participants in any clinical trial,"},{"time":429977,"text":"and establish one which is relevant for the context of the study"},{"time":435425,"text":"and most beneficial for the participants within the study."}]},{"cues":[{"time":438922,"text":"That brings us to the third point I want you think about:"},{"time":442173,"text":"the ethical review of research."},{"time":445024,"text":"An effective system for reviewing the ethical suitability"},{"time":448823,"text":"of clinical trials is primordial to safeguard participants"},{"time":452951,"text":"within any clinical trial."},{"time":455064,"text":"Unfortunately, this is often lacking"},{"time":457976,"text":"or inefficient in a lot of developing countries."},{"time":461504,"text":"Local governments need to set up effective systems"},{"time":465867,"text":"for reviewing the ethical issues around the clinical trials"},{"time":468744,"text":"which are authorized in different developing countries,"},{"time":472661,"text":"and they need to do this by setting up"},{"time":474935,"text":"ethical review committees that are independent"},{"time":477445,"text":"of the government and research sponsors."},{"time":480830,"text":"Public accountability needs to be promoted"},{"time":483240,"text":"through transparency and independent review"},{"time":486473,"text":"by nongovernmental and international organizations"},{"time":489512,"text":"as appropriate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":491083,"text":"The final point I would like for you to consider tonight"},{"time":494593,"text":"is what happens to participants in the clinical trial"},{"time":497816,"text":"once the research has been completed."},{"time":500591,"text":"I think it is absolutely wrong for research to begin"},{"time":504065,"text":"in the first place without a clear plan"},{"time":506577,"text":"for what would happen to the participants"},{"time":508656,"text":"once the trial has ended."},{"time":511096,"text":"Now, researchers need to make every effort to ensure that"},{"time":516224,"text":"an intervention that has been shown to be beneficial"},{"time":519208,"text":"during a clinical trial"},{"time":520940,"text":"is accessible to the participants of the trial"},{"time":524552,"text":"once the trial has been completed."},{"time":527100,"text":"In addition, they should be able to consider the possibility"},{"time":530624,"text":"of introducing and maintaining effective treatments"},{"time":534225,"text":"in the wider community once the trial ends."},{"time":538066,"text":"If, for any reason, they feel that this might not be possible,"},{"time":541489,"text":"then I think they should have to ethically justify"},{"time":544456,"text":"why the clinical trial should be conducted in the first place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":548483,"text":"Now, fortunately for Celine,"},{"time":550799,"text":"our meeting did not end in my office."},{"time":553474,"text":"I was able to get her enrolled into a free HIV treatment program"},{"time":557848,"text":"closer to her home,"},{"time":559236,"text":"and with a support group to help her cope."},{"time":563010,"text":"Her story has a positive ending,"},{"time":565344,"text":"but there are thousands of others in similar situations"},{"time":569047,"text":"who are much less fortunate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":571344,"text":"Although she may not know this,"},{"time":573768,"text":"my encounter with Celine has completely changed the way"},{"time":577633,"text":"in which I view HIV clinical trials in developing countries,"},{"time":581904,"text":"and made me even more determined to be part of the movement"},{"time":585624,"text":"to change the way in which things are done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":588481,"text":"I believe that every single person"},{"time":590849,"text":"listening to me tonight can be part of that change."},{"time":595224,"text":"If you are a researcher, I hold you"},{"time":597821,"text":"to a higher standard of moral conscience,"},{"time":600391,"text":"to remain ethical in your research,"},{"time":602818,"text":"and not compromise human welfare in your search for answers."},{"time":606306,"text":"If you work for a funding agency or pharmaceutical company,"},{"time":609984,"text":"I challenge you to hold your employers"},{"time":613014,"text":"to fund research that is ethically sound."},{"time":616189,"text":"If you come from a developing country like myself,"},{"time":619375,"text":"I urge you to hold your government"},{"time":622447,"text":"to a more thorough review of the clinical trials"},{"time":625063,"text":"which are authorized in your country."},{"time":627976,"text":"Yes, there is a need for us to find a cure for HIV,"},{"time":631644,"text":"to find an effective vaccine for malaria,"},{"time":634296,"text":"to find a diagnostic tool that works for T.B.,"},{"time":638138,"text":"but I believe that we owe it to those who willingly"},{"time":641713,"text":"and selflessly consent to participate in these clinical trials"},{"time":645768,"text":"to do this in a humane way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":647994,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}